main event: A luminous object was observed in the sky over Piedmont, Alabama on 4 May 1965, initially identified as a satellite (ECHO I).
interesting points: The object was described as starlike and rising overhead in the western sky,The observation lasted for about 10 minutes,The sighting was assessed by various authorities and initially concluded as a satellite, but some reports suggested it might be a natural phenomenon,There were conflicting opinions on whether the object was military or commercial,The sighting remains categorized as 'Unknown' by Project Blue Book in another report.
sighted object: a starlike object in the sky
witness description: Mr. Robert Chambers, Identification Officer, Alabama Police Dept.
